claim.claim-text:
A harvester comprising a wrapping system (360) comprising:
a pair of parallel positioned and oppositely facing sidewalls;
a plurality of rolls positioned between the sidewalls and operably linked to a subframe (361), said subframe (361) defining a space within which a net wrap device is positioned;
a supporting arm (362) radially mounted on at least one sidewall about at least one pivot point (363); wherein at least one length of the supporting arm (362) and the subframe (361) are capable of radial movement about the at least one pivot point (363) from a wrapping position to one or a plurality of non-wrapping positions;
wherein the plurality of rolls comprise:
at least one belt roll (365a - 365c), around which one or a plurality of baling belts are operably rotating and capable of endless rotation; wherein the at least one belt roll (365a-365c) is capable of exacting tension in the baling belts at least one position of the supporting arm (362); and
at least one compression roll (364a - 364b), wherein the radial movement facilitates transfer of a bale from one position to a second position by contact of the compression roll (364a- 364b) to the bale during transfer.

The harvester of any of claims 1-3, wherein the radial movement facilitates transfer of a bale from at least a first bale chamber (310) to a second position; such bale chamber having an entry point at its front end and an outlet on its rear end; wherein the subframe (361) is operably synchronized with the transfer of a bale from the bale chamber such that:
in the wrapping position, the subframe (361) is in its maximally downward position at least partially occluding the bale outlet and preventing the transfer of the bale from the bale chamber;
in at least a first raised position, the subframe (361) moves forward and upward from the wrapping position, allowing the transfer of the bale from the bale chamber to a second positon; and
in at least a second raised position, the subframe (361) moves rearward and downward from the at least a first raised position, to assist in the transfer of the bale from the bale chamber;
and optionally wrapping the bale.

The harvester of claim 6 further comprising:
a harvesting assembly positioned at the front end of the harvester and operably connected to the first bale chamber (310);
a first serpentine system (330) arranged for the first bale chamber (310), the first serpentine system (330) comprising:
a second bale gate (332) positioned in the first bale chamber (310), the second bale gate (332) comprising at least one arm element and at least one roll (334) attached thereto;
wherein the at least one arm element is mounted on at least one sidewall about at least one pivot point (333); wherein the second bale gate (332) exacts tension on the one or plurality of baling belts (331); wherein the second bale gate (332) is capable of radial movement from a closed position to one or a plurality of open positions; and wherein the radial movement facilitates the transfer of a bale from the first bale chamber (310) into the second bale chamber (320);
one or more baling belts (331) in operable contact with the at least one roll (334) of the second bale gate (332) and a plurality of stationary rollers (312a - 312b), around which the one or more baling belts (331) are capable of endless rotation; and
a second serpentine system (340) arranged for the second bale chamber (320), the second serpentine system (340) comprising:
a third bale gate (342) positioned at the outlet of the second bale chamber (320), the third bale gate (342) comprising at least one pair of arms (343), at least one pair of fixed members (348) operably connected to the at least one pair of arms (343), and at least two movable rollers (347a - 347d); wherein the at least one pair of arms (343) is mounted on at least one sidewall about at least two pivot points (345, 346); wherein the third bale gate (342) exacts tension on the one or plurality of baling belts (341); wherein the third bale gate (342) is capable of radial movement from a closed position to one or a plurality of open positions; and wherein the radial movement facilitates the ejection of a bale from the second bale chamber (320);
one or more baling belts (341) in operable contact with the at least two movable rollers (347a - 347d) of the third bale gate (342) and a plurality of stationary rollers (321), around which the one or more baling belts are capable of endless rotation.

The harvester of any of claims 7 - 10, further comprising at least a first, second, third and fourth operable conditions, wherein:
the first operable condition comprises the second bale gate (332) in a closed position, and the third bale gate (342) in a closed position, wherein the second bale gate (332) in the closed position facilitates formation of harvested crop material into a bale of a predetermined size, wherein the third bale gate (342) in the fully closed position allows second bale to exist in the second bale chamber (320);
the second operable condition comprises the second bale gate (332) in an open position, and the first bale gate (352) in a raised position, wherein the second bale gate (332) in an open position, and the first bale gate (352) in the raised position allow for the transfer of a bale from the first bale chamber (310) to the second bale chamber (320);
the third operable condition comprises the second bale gate (332) in an open position, the first bale gate (352) in a lowered position, and the third bale gate (342) in a closed position, wherein the second bale gate (332) in the open position, the first bale gate (352) in the lowered position, and the third bale gate (342) in the closed position allow for crop to be transferred from the harvesting assembly, through the first bale chamber (310), and into the second bale chamber (320);
the fourth operable condition comprises the third bale gate (342) in an open position, wherein the third bale gate (342) in the open position allow for the evacuation of a bale from the harvester.

The harvester of any of claims 6 - 12, wherein the first bale gate (352) comprises:
a first pair of arm elements extending transversely from and fixed to a first pair of pivot points on the parallel positioned and oppositely facing sidewalls;
a second pair of arm elements extending transversely from and fixed to a second pair of pivot points on the parallel positioned and oppositely facing sidewalls;
at least one pair of fixed members positioned at a distance defined by the length of the first and second pair of arms; and
at least one pair of parallel bars fixed to the one or more fixed members.

A method of harvesting material in the harvester of any of claims 1-13, said method comprising:
(a) feeding material from a harvesting assembly into the first bale chamber (310);
(b) forming a bale in the first bale chamber (310) to a desired size;
(c) transferring the partially formed bale from the first bale chamber (310) to the second bale chamber (320);
(d) completing bale formation in the second bale chamber (320);
(e) ejecting the complete bale from the second bale chamber (320) contemporaneously with initiating step (a) in a new sequence of steps (a) through (d).
